&gt; On the other hand, Zack...the Farraday Cage might just what is needed for further research. The elimination of intrusive carrier waves signals would remove any doubt that the message received should�be authentic and not doctored or misinterpreted through our ears and brains. But this calls for�the highest ethical stance by the researcher with video being shot, etc.
&gt; IE, if you are not receiving standard AM or FM signals...then how are the voices being created? Seems like would be something worth pursuing over time.
&gt; Has anyone tried this method?
&gt; Al
&gt;
&gt; -- Zack Widup &lt;w9sz@prairienet. org&gt; wrote:
&gt;
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; A Faraday cage is supposed to stop all electromagnetic fields from
&gt; entering it. They are useful in aligning equipment when you don&#39;t want
&gt; any external RF present.
&gt;
&gt; You&#39;re right; in a Faraday cage you would not be able to hear any radio
&gt; stations. Frank&#39;s box probably wouldn&#39;t work as expected in a Faraday
&gt; cage.
&gt;
&gt; Zack
&gt;
&gt; On Sun, 9 Nov 2008, threadsintyme@ juno.com wrote:
&gt;
&gt;&gt; Mike didn&#39;t cover the reasoning behind the Faraday Box in his YOUTUBE
&gt;&gt; video...is it to prevent unwanted signals to come through? Seems like
&gt;&gt; the Faraday Box could be self defeating... IE, if you are expecting
&gt;&gt; radios signals to &quot;come through&quot;, how can they?
&gt;&gt; Again, this leads back to the questioning whether it is the signals or
&gt;&gt; the noise and the effects that spirits use to communicate with? IF
&gt;&gt; spirits are using EVP&#39;s to communicate! I am still open to the
&gt;&gt; possibility that spirits are. Doesn&#39;t mean the spirits ARE...LOL.
&gt;&gt; Al
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; -- &quot;ourobouros2k2&quot; &lt;ourobouros2k2@ yahoo.com&gt; wrote:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; This would seem to illustrate the divergence between schools of
&gt;&gt; thought with traditional evp and itc/rtsc. While using a faraday cage
&gt;&gt; to to prevent spurious and unwanted RF signals from contaminating a
&gt;&gt; microphone would be helpful for traditional evp, would it not be
&gt;&gt; counterproductive for box type ITC/RTSC? I am not trying to be
&gt;&gt; sarcastic or anything, I am just wondering if the idea here is to
&gt;&gt; ensure that if anything did make it through that it would most likely
&gt;&gt; be genuine? I would be afraid that the RF shielding would be too
&gt;&gt; effective thus blocking communication with a linear sweep box. If you
&gt;&gt; did get communication from a box in a faraday cage, it would certainly
&gt;&gt; make the skeptics and cynics be forced to present new arguments.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; thanks,
&gt;&gt; Andy
