&gt;&gt;&gt; While reading a book about spirit communication, there was a chapter
&gt;&gt;&gt; which referenced the Faraday Cage. So... after reading it I decided to
&gt;&gt;&gt; try out what the book suggested and placed my Radio Shack Hack 12-470
&gt;&gt;&gt; Ghost Box into my microwave oven (in the OFF position) and ran a sweep
&gt;&gt;&gt; in the AM and FM mode.
&gt;&gt;&gt; The AM mode did receive much less but a few audio snippets did make
&gt;&gt;&gt; their way through. The FM mode was a different story. No frequencies
&gt;&gt;&gt; at all made it through... just white noise as each FM frequency was
&gt;&gt;&gt; reached during the sweep.
&gt;&gt;&gt; As I always do... I made a short video of both modes being sweeped.
&gt;&gt;&gt; You can see it, here:
